1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Ever wonder why you sweat?

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,800
It's your body's secret weapon against heat.

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,800
When your body heats up, it triggers sweat glands to release moisture onto your skin.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,800
But here's the twist: that sweat doesn't cool you directly.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,400
It's all about evaporation.

6
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:20,400
As sweat evaporates, it takes heat away from your skin.

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:26,000
This process is called evaporative cooling, and it keeps your body temperature just right.

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,800
Next time you sweat, remember: it's your body’s way of keeping cool.

9
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,000
Tap to learn more about your amazing biology!
